description:
&lt;p&gt;Salisbury NHS Foundation Trust are looking for HCPC registered Biomedical Scientists with experience in Microbiology to join their team. Microbiology at Salisbury is in an exciting phase of development with great potential and we are looking for enthusiastic and motivated team members to work with us whilst we pursue new developments. You must have HCPC registration, preferably for a minimum of two years experience, although we will consider those will slightly less experience provided confidence and practical familiarity with microbiology can be demonstrated.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be trustworthy, hardworking and adaptive. Technical and communication skills are essential as well as the ability to work to UKAS requirements of quality standards. Working as an integral part of the laboratory team you will process clinical specimens for microbiological testing and interpret the results of laboratory tests and diagnostic processes, helping to deliver a high level of service quality, both to the Trust and the community. The successful candidate will rotate through all areas of the Microbiology laboratory.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your core hours will be from 09:00 to 17:30 Monday to Friday (37.5 hours per week). Working on Saturdays, Sundays and Bank Holidays, on a rotational basis, is additionally required for this post. The post holder is required to participate in the on-call (out-of-hours) service provision. This post will also require participation in the covid-19 shift system currently 09:00 - 22:00, however, review of department working hours is currently being undertaken with a view to deliver a 24/7 service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Joanne Harris Microbiology Laboratory Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;joanne.harris7@nhs.net 01722 429099 &lt;/p&gt;
